herever possible.\n- Existing `.eqx` files should use a compatibility load plan: reconstruct the old template only for known legacy artifacts, then emit or reference a companion `model.graph.json` / manifest. Do not assume arbitrary old checkpoints can be blindly converted after Feedbax changes internal PyTree shape.\n\n## Related Issues\n\n- Feedbax `07c0ec9` â€” core graph-template/staged-model deprecation umbrella.\n- Feedbax `5c6b294` â€” seeded RLRMP Studio artifact path/loadability support.\n- RLRMP `2ef67ca` â€” older pre-migration training runs.\n- RLRMP `2092cb5` â€” legacy eval script relocation.\n\n---\nCo-Authored-By: Codex (GPT-5) \u003ccodex@openai.com\u003e","files":null}]}